content.text:
The issue was that `ImportOrderingRule` was incorrectly inserting blank lines before the first import when the `ij_kotlin_imports_layout` configuration contained blank line separators (`|`) prior to the group matching the first import.

The logic in `ImportOrderingRule.kt` iterates through imports and checks for blank line patterns between the "previous" import's group index and the "current" import's group index. For the first import, the "previous" import is `null`, and its group index is effectively `-1`. If the first import matches a group later in the layout (e.g. `java.**` at index 3) and there are `|` separators before it (e.g. at index 1), the rule would incorrectly insert a blank line at the very beginning of the import list.

I fixed this by modifying the logic to skip the blank line check when `prev` is `null`. This ensures that we only insert blank lines *between* imports, as intended, and not before the first import.

I verified the fix by creating a reproduction test case that mimicked the user's scenario and asserting that no lint violations occur (and thus no unwanted reformatting). I also ran existing tests to ensure no regressions.

File modified:
`ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/ImportOrderingRule.kt`

